# Sketch→Sculpt — Developer Handoff & Setup Guide

This document defines the required environment setup, third-party account ownership,
and validation checklist for working on the Sketch→Sculpt project.

Failure to follow this document means the developer is not approved to continue work.

---

## ENVIRONMENT FILE TEMPLATE

**File name:** `.env.local`

- This file is local only
- Never committed to git
- All values must be provided by the developer using their own accounts

```env
# ===============================
# SKETCH→SCULPT ENV TEMPLATE
# ===============================

# --- App ---
NODE_ENV=development
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# --- Supabase ---
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_PUBLIC_ANON_KEY
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
JWT_SECRET=YOUR_JWT_SECRET

# --- Storage ---
SUPABASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=artwork-images

# --- Stripe ---
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
ACCOUNT SETUP & KEY MANAGEMENT (MANDATORY)
All third-party services must be created and managed under the developer’s own accounts.
No shared logins.
No requesting keys from the project owner.
No reuse of existing credentials.
SUPABASE SETUP
Create or log into a Supabase account
Create a new project for this app
Enable Email authentication
Required Keys (Project Settings → API):
Project URL
anon public key
service_role key
Database Required tables:
artworks
artwork_versions
public_gallery
Storage
Create bucket: artwork-images
Security
Enable Row Level Security (RLS)
Policies must allow:
Insert for authenticated users
Public select for gallery display
STRIPE SETUP (TEST MODE)
Create or log into a Stripe account
Switch to Test Mode
Keys (Developers → API Keys):
Publishable key
Secret key
Webhook
Create webhook endpoint
Copy webhook signing secret
OPENAI SETUP
Create or log into an OpenAI account
Generate a new API key
DEVELOPER VALIDATION CHECKLIST
The developer must confirm all of the following:
Application runs locally using their own credentials
No placeholder values remain in .env.local
No secrets are committed to git
Original upload works
Refined stage renders
3D render stage completes
Gallery displays all stages
Stripe test payments function correctly
No direct fetch('/api/...') calls bypass safeFetch
Failures must be documented with logs and file paths.
REQUIRED DELIVERABLES
The developer must provide:
Screenshot of the app running locally
Screenshot of gallery with rendered stages
List of blockers (if any) with file paths
Clear recommendation for next steps
OWNERSHIP STATEMENT
All credentials used during development are owned and managed by the developer.
No production, personal, or private keys will be requested from the project owner.# --- AI ---
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxx
